\C[6]Jesus and his disciples went away to Lake

had come from Galilee, from Judea, from
Jerusalem, from the territory of Idumea, from
\C[6]the territory on the east side of the Jordan,
and from the region around the cities of Tyre
and Sidon. All these people came to Jesus
because they had heard of the things he was
\C[6]doing. The crowd was so large that Jesus told
his disciples to get a boat ready for him, so
that the people would not crush him.
